  "solution": [
    "## Solutions to Logarithmic and Trigonometric Functions Exercises",
    "",
    "### Exercise 1: Logarithmic Functions - Basic Properties",
    "",
    "**a)** Both increase from -∞ to ∞, steeper for smaller base",
    "",
    "**b)** Natural log, base e ≈ 2.718, similar shape to log₁₀",
    "",
    "**c)** Larger base → flatter curve near x=1",
    "",
    "**d)** Domain: (0,∞), Range: ℝ",
    "",
    "**e)** Vertical asymptote x=0",
    "",
    "### Exercise 2: Logarithmic Functions - Key Values",
    "",
    "**a)** 0, 1, 2, -1",
    "",
    "**b)** 0, 1, 2, -1",
    "",
    "**c)** 0, 1, 2, 3, 4",
    "",
    "**d)** 0, 1, 2, 3",
    "",
    "**e)** 3, -2, 1/2",
    "",
    "### Exercise 3: Logarithmic Identities",
    "",
    "**a)** Let log_a x = m, log_a y = n → x = a^m, y = a^n → xy = a^{m+n}",
    "",
    "**b)** log_a x = m, log_a y = n → x/y = a^{m-n}",
    "",
    "**c)** log_a x = m → x = a^m → x^n = a^{mn} → log_a (x^n) = mn = n log_a x",
    "",
    "**d)** log_a 1 = log_a (a^0) = 0",
    "",
    "**e)** log_a a = log_a (a^1) = 1",
    "",
    "### Exercise 4: Change of Base Formula",
    "",
    "**a)** Let log_b x = k → x = b^k → log_a x = log_a (b^k) = k log_a b → k = log_a x / log_a b",
    "",
    "**b)** log₂ 3 = log₁₀ 3 / log₁₀ 2 ≈ 0.477/0.301 ≈ 1.585",
    "",
    "**c)** ln 5 = log₁₀ 5 / log₁₀ e ≈ 0.699/0.434 ≈ 1.609",
    "",
    "**d)** log₅ 7 = ln 7 / ln 5 ≈ 1.946/1.609 ≈ 1.209",
    "",
    "**e)** Numerical verification shows consistency",
    "",
    "### Exercise 5: Logarithmic Equations",
    "",
    "**a)** x = 10² = 100",
    "",
    "**b)** x = e¹ = e",
    "",
    "**c)** x+1 = 2³ = 8 → x = 7",
    "",
    "**d)** 2x-1 = 3² = 9 → 2x = 10 → x = 5",
    "",
    "**e)** x²-1 = e⁰ = 1 → x² = 2 → x = ±√2",
    "",
    "### Exercise 6: Trigonometric Functions - Unit Circle",
    "",
    "**a)** sin θ = opposite/hypotenuse, cos θ = adjacent/hypotenuse",
    "",
    "**b)** 0, 1/2, √2/2, √3/2, 1",
    "",
    "**c)** 1, √3/2, √2/2, 1/2, 0",
    "",
    "**d)** 0, √3/3, 1, √3, undefined",
    "",
    "**e)** sin: wave from -1 to 1, cos: wave from 1 to -1",
    "",
    "### Exercise 7: Trigonometric Identities",
    "",
    "**a)** From Pythagorean theorem on unit circle",
    "",
    "**b)** Definition of tangent",
    "",
    "**c)** 90°-θ is complementary angle",
    "",
    "**d)** Same as above",
    "",
    "**e)** Geometric proof using unit circle",
    "",
    "### Exercise 8: Trigonometric Functions - Graphs",
    "",
    "**a)** Sine wave, amplitude 1, period 2π",
    "",
    "**b)** Cosine wave, amplitude 1, period 2π, phase shift π/2",
    "",
    "**c)** Tangent function with vertical asymptotes at π/2 + kπ",
    "",
    "**d)** Reciprocal functions with vertical asymptotes",
    "",
    "**e)** All have period 2π except tan (period π)",
    "",
    "### Exercise 9: Trigonometric Equations",
    "",
    "**a)** x = 30°, 150°",
    "",
    "**b)** x = 150°, 210°",
    "",
    "**c)** x = 45°",
    "",
    "**d)** x = 45°, 135°, 225°, 315°",
    "",
    "**e)** cos x = -1/2 → x = 120°, 240°",
    "",
    "### Exercise 10: Inverse Trigonometric Functions",
    "",
    "**a)** arcsin x: [-1,1] → [-π/2, π/2]",
    "",
    "**b)** Odd function, S-shape from -π/2 to π/2",
    "",
    "**c)** arccos x: [-1,1] → [0, π]",
    "",
    "**d)** Decreasing from (1,0) to (-1,π)",
    "",
    "**e)** arctan x: ℝ → (-π/2, π/2)",
    "",
    "### Exercise 11: Logarithmic Inequalities",
    "",
    "**a)** x > 10",
    "",
    "**b)** 0 < x ≤ 1",
    "",
    "**c)** x-1 < 8 → x < 9",
    "",
    "**d)** 2x+1 ≥ 3 → x ≥ 1",
    "",
    "**e)** x²-4 > 1 → x < -√5 or x > √5 (since x² > 5)",
    "",
    "### Exercise 12: Trigonometric Inequalities",
