    "**e)** Log scales show exponential growth linearly",
    "",
    "### Exercise 14: Applications - Trigonometry in Physics",
    "",
    "**a)** Maximum range at 45° launch angle",
    "",
    "**b)** Frequency f = ω/2π, period T = 2π/ω",
    "",
    "**c)** Wave speed v = ω/k, wavelength λ = 2π/k",
    "",
    "**d)** Current I = I₀ sin(ωt + φ)",
    "",
    "**e)** n₁ sin θ₁ = n₂ sin θ₂",
    "",
    "### Exercise 15: Exponential-Logarithmic Relationships",
    "",
    "**a)** Let log_a x = k → x = a^k → a^k = x",
    "",
    "**b)** Let a^x = m → log_a m = x",
    "",
    "**c)** Let ln x = k → x = e^k",
    "",
    "**d)** Let e^x = m → ln m = x",
    "",
    "**e)** Take logarithm of both sides to solve"
